issue_body:
Hi,
  I try to use deviation statement to annotate some unsupported data node as follow:

here is the test.yang
```

module test {
  yang-version 1.1;

  namespace urn:test;

  prefix test;
  
  container test-root {
    list test-root-child {
      key name;

      leaf name {
        type string;
      }

      leaf state {
        type leafref {
          path "../../test-root-child-state/name";
        }
      }
    }

    list test-root-child-state {
      key name;

      leaf name {
        type string;
      }
    }
  }
}
``` 

here is the test-dev.yang
```
module test-dev {
  yang-version 1.1;

  namespace urn:test-dev;

  prefix test-dev;

  import test {
    prefix t;
  }
  
  deviation /t:test-root/t:test-root-child/t:state {
    deviate not-supported;
  }

  deviation /t:test-root/t:test-root-child-state {
    deviate not-supported;
  }
}
```

when use the following command to apply the deviation:
```
pyang test.yang --deviation-module=test-dev.yang -f tree
test.yang:18: error: test:test-root-child-state in the path for state at test.yang:16 is not found
module: test
   +--rw test-root
      +--rw test-root-child* [name]
         +--rw name    string
```
the tree from the command  is correct, but there is error message indicates the data node is not found.
I guess the error message is unexpected.

if only the `test-root-child-state` is deviated as `not-supported`, there is no further check if any leafref point to data node deviated:

```
module test-dev {
  yang-version 1.1;

  namespace urn:test-dev;

  prefix test-dev;

  import test {
    prefix t;
  }
  deviation /t:test-root/t:test-root-child-state {
    deviate not-supported;
  }
}
```

```
pyang test.yang --deviation-module=test-dev.yang -f tree
module: test
   +--rw test-root
      +--rw test-root-child* [name]
         +--rw name     string
         +--rw state?   -> ../../test-root-child-state/name
```

here is the version information:
```
$ python --version
Python 3.5.1
$ pyang --version
pyang 1.7
```

